codex
Applied one narrow boundary-focused improvement for the latest miss (`How do I improve it?` misrouted to `OUT_OF_SCOPE`).

I added targeted contrastive examples in the CLARIFICATION-vs-OUT_OF_SCOPE extra training pack:
- 4 new ambiguous “How do I improve …” `CLARIFICATION` samples
- 2 paired “How do I improve …” but explicitly high-stakes/illegal `OUT_OF_SCOPE` samples

Then I regenerated SFT files so the next train run actually consumes this change. This keeps the experiment comparable and directly targets the current weak boundary without changing output format or reintroducing class-balanced loss.

Files changed:
- [data/processed/train_clarification_oos_boundary_pack.json](C:\Users\jhand\Documents\Github\AiLanguageCore\data\processed\train_clarification_oos_boundary_pack.json)
